      "amount": "",
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "name": "1/4 cup of chopped fresh parsley",
      "amount": "",
      "notes": "for garnish"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 425°F (220°C).",
    "Brush the phyllo dough with olive oil and season with sumac.",
    "Arrange the phyllo in a single layer on a baking sheet.",
    "Char the cauliflower florets in a skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Transfer the charred cauliflower to a baking sheet and set aside.",
    "Layer the phyllo on top of the cauliflower, brushing with olive oil between each layer.",
    "Top with burrata cheese and season with salt and pepper.",
    "Bake in the preheated oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown.",
    "Garnish with chopped parsley and serve hot."
